      <!-- 10. Future Work -->
      <section class="mb-20">
        <p class="text-[11px] font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.15em] text-[var(--color-p-blue)] mb-4">10. Future Work</p>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[var(--color-warm-text)] mb-6">Open Problems</h2>
        <div class="space-y-4 text-lg leading-[1.8] text-[var(--color-warm-text)]">
          <p>
            <strong>Fleet deployment monitoring.</strong> Scaling behavioral monitoring from single-agent to fleet-level operations. Detecting emergent behavioral patterns across robot populations and correlating drift across shared environments.
          </p>
          <p>
            <strong>Real-world behavioral trials.</strong> Validating sim-to-real transfer of behavioral specifications. Measuring drift rates in physical deployments against simulation predictions. Quantifying the gap between simulated and physical behavioral consistency.
          </p>
          <p>
            <strong>Hardware-in-the-loop validation.</strong> Closing the loop between physical sensor data, behavioral drift detection, and automated therapy cycles. Verifying that corrections generated from telemetry data produce measurable improvements in physical robot behavior.
          </p>
          <p>
            <strong>Regulatory certification partnerships.</strong> Working with standards bodies to establish behavioral intelligence as a certifiable component of robot safety. Developing test suites that regulators can use to verify behavioral compliance.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

